cz.cvut.felk.cig.jcop.problem
Class OperationHistory

java.lang.Object
  cz.cvut.felk.cig.jcop.problem.OperationHistory

public class OperationHistory
extends java.lang.Object

Operation history is used to record which operations in which order were applied to get operation.

Operation history has reference to parent operation history, but not to attributes itself. Nor does attributes has reference to parent attributes. This is because garbage collector could faster free unused configurations/operationHistories from memory. Every time attributes becomes unreachable from rest of code, it could be freed, along with its operation history (usually).

Field Detail

operation

protected Operation operation
Operation used in this step of history

parent

protected OperationHistory parent
Preceding operationHistory, root has null

counter

protected long counter
Counter indicating order of this entry in history of attributes.

Root has 0, each other child has its parent counter+1.

size

protected long size
Actual size of history. This can vary from counter if history has been empties. In such case, counter remains unchanged, while size is reset to zero.

limit

public static int limit
How many items are allowed in history at most. If this number is reached, history is emptied in order to free allocated memory. Constants LIMIT_DISABLED and LIMIT_UNLIMITED are allowed values as well as any positive number.

LIMIT_DISABLED

public static final int LIMIT_DISABLED
No history is collected. Every configuration has only one OperationHistory element (with null parent).

See Also:
Constant Field Values

LIMIT_UNLIMITED

public static final int LIMIT_UNLIMITED
History is never erased. Note that this can lead to huge memory overhead as single configuration can have as many as hundred million items in history (which with about 32B for every OperationHistory object means several GB of memory).
